text:
Installation of Roadway Signage to Impact Terminal West Parking Options This Week
Entrances to the West Parking Garage and West Economy Lot will be closed temporarily during overnight work this week as crews install new overhead signs. During the work, travelers will be directed to the East Parking Garage and East Economy Lot. The exits to both lots will not be affected, and arriving passengers will be able to exit the parking areas as they normally would. The Pikes Peak Shuttle Lot will not be affected.
The work is scheduled to take place overnight on the following days:
Tuesday, Sept. 1  The West Parking Garage entrance will be closed from 10 p.m. to 1 a.m. Wednesday, Sept. 2  The West Economy Lot entrance will be closed from 1 a.m. to 5 a.m.
Source:- Denver International Airport
